The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, January 04, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE CD				 																																	(In concert with the Edmonton Symphony Orchestra)				 																																	lRecorded live at the Jubilee Auditorium in Edmonton, Canada in 1971, this is a masterful blend of rock and classical strains. Conceived and written by vocalist-pianist Gary Brooker, the album is a milestone in progressive rock music				 																THE BOOK				 																																	(Edited by Ravina Aggarwal)				 																																	lThis collection of stories and poems by contemporary authors traces life of Indias myriad mountain ranges, from history and culture of the tribal folk, to the ecological balance and memorable journeys. Writers include Ruskin Bond, Gita Mehta and Jamling Tenzing Norgay.				 																THE FILM				 																																	(Nandan II, January 4, 6.30 pm)				 																																	lSet in the wilderness of Ladakh, it tells a tale of love between a dysfunctional model and a silent stranger. Starring Koel Puri and Irrfan Khan. Followed by a discussion with the UK-based director, Ashvin Kumar.				 																THE EVENT				 																																	(Opposite Calcutta Municipal Corporation, December 4, 5, 1 pm to 8.30 pm)				 																																	lIn its 27th edition, the two-day event will feature poetry, story-reading, musical performances, street plays and seminars. Top-draw artistes will also hold a workshop at Chaplin Square from 1 pm
